==English==

===Etymology===
<!-- Brewer's Dictionary of Phrase and Fable, Centenary edition, second impression, 1971, SBN 304-93570-0, and [[w:stock exchange]] -->
Most likely from a man Van der Burse, outside whose house in [[w:Bruges|Bruges]] traders met.  Perhaps from the Latin ''[[bursa]]'' meaning [[bag]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}

'''bourse'''
# [[stock exchange]]
# A meeting of stamp collectors and/or dealers, where stamps and covers are sold or exchanged. A bourse usually has no competitive exhibits of stamps or covers. Almost all public stamp exhibitions include a dealer bourse, though many bourses are held without a corresponding exhibition.

